result.execSummary:
The defendant Curtis L Brown was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take >$500 - $5000) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Straight time.  Court grants 2 days credit if revoked.
Court does not object to transfer to Dane County if accepted.

miscConds.notes:
If Defendant completes 25 hours of community service and submits verification prior to 12/31/22, the Court will consider Standard Court Costs and DRGOD Surcharge  satisfied. Agent to make any financial adjustments.

DNA Surcharge to be paid as a condition of probation.

AODA assessment, follow through with any treatment recommended.  No use or possession of alcohol, controlled substances or illegal drugs/drug paraphernalia. Maintain absolute sobriety. No use or possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription. Any valid prescriptions must be taken only in the manner they are prescribed.

Inform Agent of all prescriptions.  Obtain or Maintain full-time employment once cleared by your doctor.  No contact with Co-Defendant or Sew Much More Store.

Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.

If probation is revoked and a prison term is not ordered, or if probation is discharged/terminated, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and government entities for outstanding financial obligations.  Collection may include income assignment.
